Git Kata
========

A simple repository to practice `git` usage

Agenda
------

* Rebase vs merging. See this <a href="https://miro.medium.com/max/662/1*75GIyh005_Wl9vRQF3tgTQ.png" target="_blank">picture</a>
* Interactive rebase. See [Changing Multiple Commit Messages](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Rewriting-History)
* Co-authors. See [Creating a commit with multiple authors](https://help.github.com/en/articles/creating-a-commit-with-multiple-authors)
* Cherry-pick. See [Cherry-pick Documentation](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-cherry-pick)
* Github code review. See [About pull request reviews](https://help.github.com/en/articles/about-pull-request-reviews)
* Reflog. See [Reflog Documentation](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-reflog)

References
----------

[Git rebase tutorial step-by-step](https://github.com/rafasantos/rafael-santos-blog/blob/master/posts/git-rebase-tutorial/README.md)

___
Remember: _Ugly code needs test the most_
